eyck.gloss: Flemish painter who was a founder of the Flemish school of painting and who pioneered modern techniques of oil painting (1390-1441)

eye-drop.gloss: a drop from an eye dropper

eye-lotion.gloss: lotion consisting of a solution used as a cleanser for the eyes

eye cup.gloss: a small vessel with a rim curved to fit the orbit of the eye

eye dropper.gloss: pipet consisting of a small tube with a vacuum bulb at one end for drawing liquid in and releasing it a drop at a time

eye muscle.gloss: one of the small muscles of the eye that serve to rotate the eyeball

eye operation.gloss: any surgical procedure involving the eyes

eye socket.gloss: the bony cavity in the skull containing the eyeball

eye surgery.gloss: any surgical procedure involving the eyes

eye tooth.gloss: one of the four pointed conical teeth (two in each jaw) located between the incisors and the premolars

eyebath.gloss: a small vessel with a rim curved to fit the orbit of the eye

eyebrow.gloss: the arch of hair above each eye

eyecup.gloss: a small vessel with a rim curved to fit the orbit of the eye

eyedrop.gloss: a drop from an eye dropper

eyeglass.gloss: lens for correcting defective vision in one eye

eyehole.gloss: a hole (in a door or an oven etc) through which you can peep
